      • isGET

        public boolean isGET()
        When true, use GET for query and otherwise use POST (default ). POST can often handle larger queries than GET due to limits at the HTTP client layer and will defeat http caching and thus provide a current view of the committed state of the SPARQL end point when the end point is a read/write database. However, GET supports HTTP caching and can scale much better when the SPARQL end point is a read-only resource or a read-mostly resource where stale reads are acceptable.

      • getSPARQLVersion

        public SPARQLVersion getSPARQLVersion()
        Description copied from interface: IServiceOptions
        Returns if SPARQLVersion.SPARQL_11 iff the end point supports SPARQL 1.1. When SPARQLVersion.SPARQL_10, the solutions will be vectored to the end point using a technique which is compatible with SPARQL 1.0.
        Returns:
        the SPARQL version SPARQLVersion
